texts:
Concept: Variables
Language: Python
Example: x = 5
Explanation: Stores a value in memory with a name

Concept: Assign Multiple
Language: Python
Example: x, y = 1, 2
Explanation: Assigns multiple variables at once

Concept: Data Types
Language: Python
Example: 5 (int), 3.14 (float), 'Hi' (str), True (bool)
Explanation: Basic kinds of values

Concept: Type Check
Language: Python
Example: type(5)  # int
Explanation: Shows the type of a value

Concept: Comments
Language: Python
Example: # This is a comment
Explanation: Notes for humans; Python ignores them

Concept: Strings
Language: Python
Example: name = 'Ana'
Explanation: Text data surrounded by quotes

Concept: String Concatenation
Language: Python
Example: 'Hi ' + 'there'
Explanation: Joins strings together

Concept: F-Strings
Language: Python
Example: name = 'Ana'; f'Hello {name}'
Explanation: Easy way to format strings

Concept: Input
Language: Python
Example: name = input('Your name: ')
Explanation: Reads text from the user

Concept: Print Output
Language: Python
Example: print('Hello')
Explanation: Shows text on the screen

Concept: Arithmetic
Language: Python
Example: 3 + 2 * 2
Explanation: Math with numbers (PEMDAS order)

Concept: Comparison
Language: Python
Example: 5 == 5  # True,Compares values (==, !=, <, >, <=
Explanation: >=)

Concept: Boolean Logic
Language: Python
Example: True and False
Explanation: Combines conditions with and/or/not

Concept: If Statement
Language: Python
Example: if x > 0:\n    print('Positive')
Explanation: Runs code only if condition is true

Concept: If/Else
Language: Python
Example: if x % 2 == 0:\n    print('Even')\nelse:\n    print('Odd')
Explanation: Chooses between two paths

Concept: Elif
Language: Python
Example: if n==0: ... elif n==1: ...
Explanation: Adds extra checks after if

Concept: While Loop
Language: Python
Example: while x < 3:\n    x += 1
Explanation: Repeats while condition stays true

Concept: For Loop
Language: Python
Example: for i in range(3):\n    print(i)
Explanation: Repeats a fixed number of times

Concept: List
Language: Python
Example: nums = [1, 2, 3]
Explanation: Stores multiple values in order

Concept: List Access
Language: Python
Example: nums[0]  # first item
Explanation: Gets a value by position

Concept: List Append
Language: Python
Example: nums.append(4)
Explanation: Adds a value to the end

Concept: Tuple
Language: Python
Example: "coords = (10, 20)",Fixed order
Explanation: cannot change

Concept: Set
Language: Python
Example: "unique = {1, 2, 3}",No duplicates
Explanation: order not guaranteed

Concept: Dictionary
Language: Python
Example: person = {'name': 'Ana', 'age': 10}
Explanation: Key-value pairs

Concept: Dict Access
Language: Python
Example: person['name']
Explanation: Gets a value by its key

Concept: Function
Language: Python
Example: def greet(name):\n    return 'Hi ' + name
Explanation: Reusable block of code

Concept: Parameters
Language: Python
Example: def add(a,b): return a+b
Explanation: Inputs a function needs

Concept: Return
Language: Python
Example: def square(n): return n*n
Explanation: Gives a result back

Concept: Scope
Language: Python
Example: x = 5\ndef f(): print(x)
Explanation: Where a variable can be used

Concept: Import Module
Language: Python
Example: import math
Explanation: Brings in extra tools

Concept: Exception Handling
Language: Python
Example: try:\n    x = 1/0\nexcept ZeroDivisionError:\n    print('Error')
Explanation: Catches errors so program keeps running

Concept: List Comprehension
Language: Python
Example: squares = [n*n for n in range(3)]
Explanation: Short way to build a list

Concept: Range
Language: Python
Example: list(range(3))  # [0,1,2]
Explanation: Sequence of numbers

Concept: Len
Language: Python
Example: len([1,2,3])  # 3
Explanation: Counts items in a list or text

Concept: Variables
Language: JavaScript
Example: let x = 5;
Explanation: Stores a value with a name

Concept: Constants
Language: JavaScript
Example: const PI = 3.14;
Explanation: Value that cannot be reassigned

Concept: Var vs Let
Language: JavaScript
Example: var x = 1; let y = 2;
Explanation: Older vs newer declarations

Concept: Data Types
Language: JavaScript
Example: 42 (number), 'hi' (string), true (boolean)
Explanation: Basic kinds of values

Concept: Comments
Language: JavaScript
Example: // note or /* block */
Explanation: Notes for humans; JS ignores them

Concept: Console Log
Language: JavaScript
Example: console.log('Hello')
Explanation: Shows text in the browser console

Concept: Arithmetic
Language: JavaScript
Example: 3 + 2 * 2
Explanation: Math with numbers

Concept: Comparison
Language: JavaScript
Example: 5 === 5  // true
Explanation: Strict equality (type + value)

Concept: If Statement
Language: JavaScript
Example: if (x > 0) { console.log('Positive'); }
Explanation: Runs code if condition is true

Concept: If/Else
Language: JavaScript
Example: if (n%2===0){...} else {...}
Explanation: Chooses between two paths

Concept: Else If
Language: JavaScript
Example: if (n===0){...} else if(n===1){...}
Explanation: Adds extra checks

Concept: For Loop
Language: JavaScript
Example: for (let i=0;i<3;i++){ console.log(i); }
Explanation: Repeats a fixed number of times

Concept: While Loop
Language: JavaScript
Example: while (x < 3) { x++; }
Explanation: Repeats while condition stays true

Concept: Arrays
Language: JavaScript
Example: let nums = [1,2,3];
Explanation: Stores multiple values in order

Concept: Array Access
Language: JavaScript
Example: nums[0]
Explanation: Gets a value by position

Concept: Array Push
Language: JavaScript
Example: nums.push(4)
Explanation: Adds a value to the end

Concept: Objects
Language: JavaScript
Example: let person = {name:'Bob', age:10};
Explanation: Key-value pairs

Concept: Object Access
Language: JavaScript
Example: person.name
Explanation: Gets a value by its key

Concept: Functions
Language: JavaScript
Example: function hi(name){ return 'Hi '+name; }
Explanation: Reusable block of code

Concept: Arrow Function
Language: JavaScript
Example: const add=(a,b)=>a+b;
Explanation: Short function syntax

Concept: Template Literals
Language: JavaScript
Example: `Hi ${name}`
Explanation: Easy string building

Concept: DOM Get Element
Language: JavaScript
Example: document.getElementById('title')
Explanation: Finds an element by id

Concept: DOM Change Text
Language: JavaScript
Example: element.innerText = 'Hello'
Explanation: Updates page text

Concept: Event Listener
Language: JavaScript
Example: button.addEventListener('click', fn)
Explanation: Run code on a click

Concept: JSON Basics
Language: JavaScript
Example: JSON.parse('{"a":1}')
Explanation: Convert text to object

Language: HTML
Example: <script src="app.js"></script>

Concept: Color
Language: CSS
Example: p { color: red; }
Explanation: Changes text color

Concept: Background
Language: CSS
Example: body { background: lightblue; }
Explanation: Sets background color

Concept: Font Size
Language: CSS
Example: h1 { font-size: 24px; }
Explanation: Sets text size

Concept: Font Family
Language: CSS
Example: p { font-family: Arial; }
Explanation: Changes the font

Concept: Text Align
Language: CSS
Example: p { text-align: center; }
Explanation: Aligns text

Concept: Width/Height
Language: CSS
Example: div { width: 200px; height: 100px; }
Explanation: Element size

Concept: Margin
Language: CSS
Example: div { margin: 10px; }
Explanation: Space outside the element

Concept: Padding
Language: CSS
Example: div { padding: 10px; }
Explanation: Space inside the element

Concept: Border
Language: CSS
Example: div { border: 1px solid black; }
Explanation: Line around the element

Concept: Border Radius
Language: CSS
Example: div { border-radius: 8px; }
Explanation: Rounded corners

Concept: Display
Language: CSS
Example: span { display: inline; } div { display:block; }
Explanation: Inline vs block layout

Concept: Inline-Block
Language: CSS
Example: div { display: inline-block; }
Explanation: Inline flow with box sizing

Concept: Class Selector
Language: CSS
Example: .btn { padding: 5px; }
Explanation: Selects by class

Concept: ID Selector
Language: CSS
Example: #main { color: blue; }
Explanation: Selects by id

Concept: Descendant Selector
Language: CSS
Example: ul li { color: green; }
Explanation: Selects nested elements

Concept: Group Selector
Language: CSS
Example: h1, h2 { color: purple; }
Explanation: Styles multiple selectors

Concept: Hover State
Language: CSS
Example: a:hover { color: orange; }
Explanation: Style when mouse hovers

Concept: Box Model
Language: CSS
Example: /* content + padding + border + margin */
Explanation: How spacing works

Concept: Units
Language: CSS
Example: div { width: 50%; padding: 1rem; },Common units: px, %
Explanation: rem

Concept: Flexbox Enable
Language: CSS
Example: div { display: flex; }
Explanation: Turns on flex layout

Concept: Flex Direction
Language: CSS
Example: div { flex-direction: row; }
Explanation: Row or column layout

Concept: Justify Content
Language: CSS
Example: div { justify-content: center; }
Explanation: Main-axis alignment

Concept: Align Items
Language: CSS
Example: div { align-items: center; }
Explanation: Cross-axis alignment

Concept: Grid Enable
Language: CSS
Example: div { display: grid; }
Explanation: Turns on grid layout

Concept: Grid Columns
Language: CSS
Example: div { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
Explanation: Two equal columns

Concept: Media Query
Language: CSS
Example: @media (max-width:600px){ body{font-size:14px;} }
Explanation: Change styles on small screens

Language: CSS
Example: <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
Explanation: Link CSS file to HTML
